-----------------------------------------

🔹 Why Repeated Prefix Sum Works?

Index 0 → sum = 4

Index 3 → sum = 4

Same prefix sum again.

Means:

(4 + 2 - 3 + 1)
-
(4)

= 0

Subarray:

[2, -3, 1]

-----------------------------------------

🔹 Visual Formula

PrefixSum(j) - PrefixSum(i) = SubarraySum

If

PrefixSum(j) = PrefixSum(i)

Then

SubarraySum = 0

-----------------------------------------

🔹 Why HashMap?

Need to quickly know:

"Have I seen this prefix sum before?"

HashMap lookup = O(1) average.

-----------------------------------------

🔹 Pattern to Remember

Prefix Sum Questions:

sum += arr[i]

if(sum == target)
    answer found

if(prefixSum already seen)
    answer found

Store current prefix sum

-----------------------------------------

🔹 Complexity

Time  : O(N)
Space : O(N)

-----------------------------------------

🔹 Interview Point

Whenever question says:

- Zero Sum Subarray
- Subarray Sum = K
- Longest Subarray Sum K
- Count Subarray Sum K

Think:

"PREFIX SUM + HASHMAP"

#Code:

import java.util.*;

public class Solution
{
    public static boolean findsum(int arr[], int n)
    {
        //You can code here

        HashMap<Integer, Integer> map = new HashMap<>();
        int sum = 0;

        for(int i=0; i<n; i++){
            sum += arr[i];

            if(sum == 0){
                return true;
            }

            if(map.containsKey(sum)){
                return true;
            }
            else{
                map.put(sum, i);
            }
        }

        return false;



    }
}
